          <name>OBJECT_BOUNDING_BOX</name>
          <briefdescription>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Uses the normals for the start, end &amp; center points, i.e. top-left is (-0.5, -0.5) and bottom-right is (0.5, 0.5). </para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1GradientVisual_1_1Units_1a49cf9c816d9cf5d26f20ce1c79ca8816ab3dfd99566031602e7d953c75ec48e31" prot="public">
          <name>USER_SPACE</name>
          <briefdescription>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Uses the user coordinates for the start, end &amp; center points, i.e. in a 200 by 200 control, top-left is (0, 0) and bottom-right is (200, 200). </para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The type of coordinate system for certain attributes of the points in a gradient. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This applies to the:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Start (x1, y1) and End (x2 and y2) points of a line if using a linear gradient.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Center point (cx, cy) and radius (r) of a circle if using a radial gradient. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
